00:15:30,672 --> 00:15:31,772
What?

308
00:15:31,772 --> 00:15:34,472
I would never do anything like that.

309
00:15:34,472 --> 00:15:37,272
If so, you must've said something to her.

310
00:15:37,272 --> 00:15:40,072
Don't you remember what you said back then?

311
00:15:40,072 --> 00:15:43,372
Back then...

312
00:15:43,372 --> 00:15:46,925
I chased her and fell

313
00:15:46,925 --> 00:15:50,372
and deeply cut the palm of my hand.

314
00:15:50,372 --> 00:15:54,172
I see. And she treated your wound for you.

315
00:15:54,172 --> 00:15:55,372
No.

316
00:15:55,372 --> 00:15:58,272
She ran off not knowing that I fell.

317
00:15:58,272 --> 00:15:59,572
Is that so?

318
00:15:59,572 --> 00:16:00,939
But...

319
00:16:00,939 --> 00:16:02,941
the cut that I got back then

320
00:16:02,941 --> 00:16:05,972
is still left like a carving here on the palm of my hand.

321
00:16:05,972 --> 00:16:08,172
Carved?

322
00:16:08,172 --> 00:16:10,472
Come to think of it, he mentioned that

323
00:16:10,472 --> 00:16:12,951
it was also written in her letter.

324
00:16:12,951 --> 00:16:17,572
"So that my feelings are carved onto your heart,"

325
00:16:17,572 --> 00:16:19,372
Directly carve on means...

326
00:16:19,372 --> 00:16:20,959
Somewhere on the body.

327
00:16:22,961 --> 00:16:24,972
I see... That's what it was!

328
00:16:30,372 --> 00:16:32,172
Conan, did you figure out?

329
00:16:32,172 --> 00:16:33,772
You figured it out, didn't you?

330
00:16:33,772 --> 00:16:35,572
Yeah, I figured out that...

331
00:16:35,572 --> 00:16:38,172
Officer Chiba used to...

332
00:16:38,172 --> 00:16:40,572
sweat a lot since he was a child!

333
00:16:40,572 --> 00:16:41,572
What?

334
00:16:41,572 --> 00:16:44,472
It's true that I sweat a lot.

335
00:16:44,472 --> 00:16:46,072
Although I wasn't as bad Genta,

336
00:16:46,072 --> 00:16:48,372
I was pretty hefty.

337
00:16:48,372 --> 00:16:51,272
What's that got to do with anything?

338
00:16:51,272 --> 00:16:52,991
When you open this lid,

339
00:16:53,172 --> 00:16:56,772
you place your hand on this side video, right?

340
00:16:56,772 --> 00:17:00,672
That's where she wrote the message with a water-based pen.

341
00:17:00,672 --> 00:17:01,972
She did so, because that way,

342
00:17:01,972 --> 00:17:04,772
the words would rub off

343
00:17:04,772 --> 00:17:06,572
on the sweaty hands of Officer Chiba.

344
00:17:06,572 --> 00:17:08,372
Moreover, she wrote it in mirrored words

345
00:17:08,372 --> 00:17:10,272
that you would be able to read it too.

346
00:17:10,272 --> 00:17:13,272
See. On my hands that I used to open the lid,

347
00:17:13,272 --> 00:17:16,272
there's red ink, isn't there? That's the proof.

348
00:17:16,272 --> 00:17:17,672
I see.

349
00:17:17,672 --> 00:17:20,472
Even if you write on the black side of the tape with red ink,

350
00:17:20,472 --> 00:17:21,772
it would not be visible.

351
00:17:21,772 --> 00:17:23,572
On top of that, it's written in a place that no one else would touch,

352
00:17:23,572 --> 00:17:26,172
so she didn't have to worry about anybody else seeing it too.

353
00:17:26,172 --> 00:17:29,672
But, it's already been 13 years, so I wonder if it's still legible?

354
00:17:29,672 --> 00:17:33,031
Don't worry. You rip the paper up like this

355
00:17:33,031 --> 00:17:35,033
and wet it with water.

356
00:17:35,272 --> 00:17:38,172
You paste it on like so on the side of the video,

357
00:17:38,172 --> 00:17:40,072
then peel it off.

358
00:17:40,072 --> 00:17:43,872
The message put here 13 years ago is revived.

359
00:17:43,872 --> 00:17:45,972
"I like you too"

360
00:17:49,572 --> 00:17:52,172
I like you too, is written here!

361
00:17:52,172 --> 00:17:53,972
You both liked each other!

362
00:17:53,972 --> 00:17:55,472
Amazing!

363
00:17:55,472 --> 00:17:57,972
When's the reunion that she's coming to?

364
00:17:57,972 --> 00:18:00,172
Tonight.

365
00:18:00,172 --> 00:18:02,572
Then, maybe you should go?

366
00:18:02,572 --> 00:18:06,072
But, I wonder about telling her at this point that I got her message.

367
00:18:06,072 --> 00:18:09,067
No! You should go!

368
00:18:09,067 --> 00:18:12,672
Her feelings finally reached you after 13 years, you know?

369
00:18:12,672 --> 00:18:15,073
Of course she'd be happy.

370
00:18:15,073 --> 00:18:17,075
Ms. Kobayashi?

371
00:18:17,075 --> 00:18:20,472
I'm sorry. I overheard you.

372
00:18:25,672 --> 00:18:29,372
What I like is not SFX but...

373
00:18:29,372 --> 00:18:32,472
Don't make me say it, stupid!

374
00:18:34,772 --> 00:18:37,095
What? Ms. Miike's not here?

375
00:18:37,095 --> 00:18:39,672
No, she says she came up with an urgent matter.

376
00:18:39,672 --> 00:18:43,101
She seemed really happy saying that she finally got together

377
00:18:43,101 --> 00:18:45,472
with the one she really cared for after hoping for so long.

378
00:18:45,472 --> 00:18:47,105
She got together?

379
00:18:47,105 --> 00:18:50,172
I wonder. Maybe she got married or something?

380
00:18:58,172 --> 00:19:00,772
What should I tell the children?

381
00:19:04,572 --> 00:19:07,125
No way, a parking violation.

382
00:19:07,372 --> 00:19:08,672
I was planning to come back

383
00:19:08,672 --> 00:19:10,472
and re-park the car as soon as I saw her.

384
00:19:10,472 --> 00:19:13,131
But, I was plodding along from shock.

385
00:19:13,131 --> 00:19:15,133
Excuse me...

386
00:19:15,133 --> 00:19:19,137
Don't worry about it, I haven't sent the data yet.

387
00:19:19,137 --> 00:19:20,872
You left the engine on so you

388
00:19:20,872 --> 00:19:23,141
were planning to come back right away, weren't you?

389
00:19:23,141 --> 00:19:24,272
Yes...

390
00:19:24,272 --> 00:19:25,872
Besides, being a police detective

391
00:19:25,872 --> 00:19:28,272
there are times you may have to inevitably park, so...

392
00:19:28,272 --> 00:19:29,772
No.

393
00:19:29,772 --> 00:19:31,149
No matter if you're an officer or not,

394
00:19:31,149 --> 00:19:32,872
a parking violation is a violation.

395
00:19:32,872 --> 00:19:34,772
You've got to do your job.

396
00:19:36,772 --> 00:19:40,372
Well, it's not like I came for an investigation or anything besides.

397
00:19:40,372 --> 00:19:43,161
Then, I'll go pay for the violation

398
00:19:43,161 --> 00:19:45,572
so will you give me the violation ticket?

399
00:19:45,572 --> 00:19:46,872
Yes, sir.

400
00:19:51,169 --> 00:19:53,171
I tried to act cool,

401
00:19:53,372 --> 00:19:56,972
but the charge for violation 15,000 yen sure isn't cheap.

402
00:19:56,972 --> 00:20:01,172
But, I wonder how she knew I was a police detective?

403
00:20:01,172 --> 00:20:02,472
What's the matter?

404
00:20:02,472 --> 00:20:03,872
Did that guy who got the parking violation

405
00:20:03,872 --> 00:20:05,572
give you trouble or something?

406
00:20:05,572 --> 00:20:07,185
No...

407
00:20:07,185 --> 00:20:09,187
By the way, is it really okay?

408
00:20:09,372 --> 00:20:11,172
Not attending the reunion?

409
00:20:11,172 --> 00:20:12,272
Yes.

410
00:20:12,272 --> 00:20:15,193
I haven't gone to the reunion for some time now,

411
00:20:15,372 --> 00:20:18,672
so I think I'd feel uncomfortable even if I went anyway.

412
00:20:18,672 --> 00:20:19,872
And...

413
00:20:19,872 --> 00:20:23,672
I got to see the person that I really wanted see too.

414
00:20:23,672 --> 00:20:29,207
Well, it seems that he had forgotten all about me though.

415
00:20:29,207 --> 00:20:30,872
Are you talking about...

416
00:20:30,872 --> 00:20:32,272
the childhood friend of yours that is a police detective

417
00:20:32,272 --> 00:20:34,772
at the Tokyo Metropolitan Police Department?

418
00:20:34,772 --> 00:20:35,872
Yes.

419
00:20:35,872 --> 00:20:37,215
I'm going to be transferred to the

420
00:20:37,215 --> 00:20:39,672
headquarters of the Police Department soon,

421
00:20:39,672 --> 00:20:41,872
so I'll be able to work with him.

422
00:20:41,872 --> 00:20:44,672
I was planning to tell him how I felt at that time,

423
00:20:44,672 --> 00:20:46,772
if I met him and he remembered me but...

424
00:20:46,772 --> 00:20:49,227
I guess life just doesn't work out that way.

425
00:20:49,227 --> 00:20:52,872
Gosh, to forget a great lady like you.

426
00:20:52,872 --> 00:20:56,372
He's probably not worth anything, forget him.

427
00:20:56,372 --> 00:20:58,772
It's not that he's not worth it.

428
00:20:58,772 --> 00:21:01,572
He's as cute and childish looking as ever.

429
00:21:02,872 --> 00:21:04,072
Besides...

430
00:21:04,072 --> 00:21:06,772
I was the youngest child in the family

431
00:21:06,772 --> 00:21:09,572
and was really pampered by my parents and was never scolded.

432
00:21:09,572 --> 00:21:12,072
But, back then he...

433
00:21:12,072 --> 00:21:14,172
I'll go home ahead of you.

434
00:21:14,172 --> 00:21:16,372
Because I have a TV program I want to watch.

435
00:21:16,372 --> 00:21:18,172
Don't cross now.

436
00:21:19,257 --> 00:21:21,259
The traffic light's red.

437
00:21:21,259 --> 00:21:27,265
Who cares? There are no cars and nobody's watching.

438
00:21:27,265 --> 00:21:31,269
I'm watching. And you're watching too.

